<paragraph id="8B9DCE77FFE60C60609FFDA0FD16FD69" blockId="3.[174,1233,628,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Mesonotum and pleura mostly black, scutellum yellow. Wing with wide preapical crossband (
<figureCitation id="1319D2F2FFE60C606216FD41FD1DFD28" box="[618,673,660,686]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[250,1160,854,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-234@1.[208,1191,839,1746]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Flies of the tribe Myopitini (1–2, 4–6): (1, 2, 4 — habitus, left; 5 — head, left, enlarged; 6 — wing): 1 — Eurasimona stigma, ♀; 2 — Inuromaesa maura, ♀, 3 — its host plant, Inula salicina, ♀; 4–6 — Myopites inulaedyssentericae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453587/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">fig 6</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C6062D1FD40FD07FD28" box="[685,699,661,686]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">a</emphasis>
) wider than the hyaline space between it and apical spot, broken into two spots by hyaline space on vein M; veins R 
<subScript id="17A6CC32FFE60C6063A6FD12FC48FD53" attach="left" box="[986,1012,711,725]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">4+5</subScript>
and M convergent (
<figureCitation id="1319D2F2FFE60C6060C9FD01FF50FD68" box="[181,236,724,750]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[250,1160,854,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-234@1.[208,1191,839,1746]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Flies of the tribe Myopitini (1–2, 4–6): (1, 2, 4 — habitus, left; 5 — head, left, enlarged; 6 — wing): 1 — Eurasimona stigma, ♀; 2 — Inuromaesa maura, ♀, 3 — its host plant, Inula salicina, ♀; 4–6 — Myopites inulaedyssentericae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453587/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">fig 6</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C606084FD00FEBAFD68" box="[248,262,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">a</emphasis>
); aculeus smooth (not tuberculate).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9DCE77FFE60C60609FFD20FE65FCC9" blockId="3.[174,1233,628,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
H o s t p l a n t s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C22B5F4FFE60C6061D4FD21FD26FC88" box="[424,666,756,782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pulicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dysenterica">
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C6061D4FD21FD26FC88" box="[424,666,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Pulicaria dysenterica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Bernh., 
<taxonomicName id="4C22B5F4FFE60C606352FD21FC10FC88" box="[814,940,756,782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C606352FD21FC10FC88" box="[814,940,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Inula hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName id="4C22B5F4FFE60C6063AAFD20FBFAFC88" box="[982,1094,756,782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicina">
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C6063AAFD20FBFAFC88" box="[982,1094,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">I. salicina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB3B386FFE60C60640DFD21FF54FCA9" author="Hendel, F." pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="1 - 221" refId="ref6151" refString="Hendel, F. 1927. 49. Trypetidae. In: Lindner, E., ed. Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. 5 (Lfg. 16 - 19), Sweizerbartsche Verlag, Stuttgart, 1 - 221 + I - XVII pl." type="book chapter" year="1927">Hendel, 1927</bibRefCitation>
) and possibly some other plants (records needing checking); in 
<collectingCountry id="F3358EE7FFE60C6063A1FCC0FBADFCA9" box="[989,1041,789,815]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Iran</collectingCountry>
, it was collected on 
<taxonomicName id="4C22B5F4FFE60C6060A8FCE1FE86FCC9" box="[212,314,820,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C6060A8FCE1FEAFFCC8" box="[212,275,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Inula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C22B5F4FFE60C60613CFCE1FE00FCC8" box="[320,444,820,846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicina">
cf. 
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C60611FFCE1FE00FCC8" box="[355,444,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">salicina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9DCE77FFE60C60609FFC80FF56FC29" blockId="3.[174,1233,628,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Great Britain, most of Middle Europe from northern Spain to Russia and Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB3B386FFE60C606134FCA0FDD7FC09" author="Merz, B. &amp; Korneyev, V. A." box="[328,619,884,911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" refId="ref6731" refString="Merz, B., Korneyev, V. A. 2004. Tephritidae. In: Pape, T., ed. Fauna Europea. Insecta: Diptera. Fauna Europaea version 1.1. Accessed via http: // www. faunaeur. org on 15.04. 2016." type="url" year="2004">Merz &amp; Korneyev, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), but many records need checking. 
<emphasis id="B9561265FFE60C606468FCA0FF56FC29" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
New record for 
<collectingCountry id="F3358EE7FFE60C6060D2FC40FF5AFC29" box="[174,230,917,943]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
